							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/darrowfarr/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/darrow-farr-author-100x100.jpeg" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/darrow-farr-author.jpeg 2x" alt="Darrow Farr" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/darrowfarr/">Darrow Farr</a></h6>
										Darrow Farr is a Salvadoran American writer. She was a Stegner Fellow in Fiction at Stanford University from 2017 to 2019 and received an MFA in creative writing from the Michener Center at the University of Texas. <em>The Bombshell</em> is her debut novel. She was born and raised outside Philadelphia, where she now lives with her husband and son.																			</div>
								</div><br class="clear"/><br/>
